    <!-- This section explains different special characters using HTML entities -->
    <section>
        <h2>Common Special Characters</h2>
        <p>Here are some commonly used special characters:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>&amp; (Ampersand)</li> <!-- & -->
            <li>&lt; (Less than)</li> <!-- < -->
            <li>&gt; (Greater than)</li> <!-- > -->
            <li>&copy; (Copyright)</li> <!-- © -->
            <li>&reg; (Registered Trademark)</li> <!-- ® -->
            <li>&trade; (Trademark)</li> <!-- ™ -->
        </ul>
    </section>
    
    <!-- Footer section with additional notes -->
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Your Name. All rights reserved.</p> <!-- Copyright symbol -->
        <p>Note: Special characters are represented using HTML entities to ensure they are displayed correctly in web browsers.</p>
    </footer>
